		<body>
			<div xml:id="div1" corresp="regest1">
				<p>
					<s n="1" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Gratiam et vitae innocentiam a domino.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="2" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Literas tuas<note xml:id="fn1" type="footnote" n="1">Oben <ref target="file10858">Nr. 819</ref>.</note> accepi, vir clarissime, magna cum animi laetitia; gratissima enim sunt, quae tu scribis.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="3" xml:lang="la" type="auto">De conventu Isenacensi<note xml:id="fn2" type="footnote" n="2">Zur Zusammenkunft der oberdeutschen Theologen mit <persName ref="person138">Luther</persName> in <placeName ref="place310">Eisenach</placeName> bzw. <placeName ref="place1205">Wittenberg</placeName> vgl. oben <ref target="file10877">Nr. 838</ref>, Anm. 5.</note> ne verbum interim unum audio atque ideo nescio, quid divinare possim.</s>
					<s n="4" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Utinam fallar!</s>
					<s n="5" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Vereor, ne plaustra ceremoniarum sint advecturi, pondus ingratissimum.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="6" xml:lang="la" type="auto"><pb type="edition" next="321"/>Apud nos magna quidem securitas est.</s>
					<s n="7" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Cives enim, et qui agrum incolunt, pulchre obediunt magistratui mercenariam militiam prohibenti<note xml:id="fn3" type="footnote" n="3">Zu den Maßnahmen der Zürcher Obrigkeit gegen das Reislaufen vgl. oben <ref target="file10877">Nr. 838</ref>, Anm. 3.</note>.</s>
					<s n="8" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Aliquot modo nebulones periuri cum periculo vitae eruperunt.</s>
					<s n="9" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Apud Quinquepagicos mira est turba.</s>
					<s n="10" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Verbis et verberibus mutuis sese lacessunt.</s>
					<s n="11" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Sunt enim, qui caesaris partes fovent, magnates aliquot; sed his reclamat plebs auro corrupta Gallico.</s>
					<s n="12" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Suspicantur, qui apud nos cordatiores sunt, intra aliquot dierum spatium turmatim illos sublatisque signis ad Gallum<note xml:id="fn4" type="footnote" n="4"><persName ref="person859">Franz I.</persName>, König von <placeName ref="place11">Frankreich</placeName>.</note> concessuros caesare neglecto, qui putatur illis solvisse coronatorum 6000<note xml:id="fnb" type="footnote" n="b">6000 <hi>korrigiert aus</hi> 60000 <hi>(die letzte</hi> 0 <hi>verschmiert).</hi></note>.</s>
					<s n="13" xml:lang="la" type="manual">Tigurini dolent tam misere fidem prodi et omnem disciplinam conculcari, venalia apud istos esse omnia.</s>
					<s n="14" xml:lang="la" type="auto"><placeName ref="place121">Bernates</placeName> videntur se huic malo miscuisse imprudentissime.</s>
					<s n="15" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Verum fata volentes ducunt, trahunt nolentes<note xml:id="fn5" type="footnote" n="5"><persName ref="person2152">Seneca</persName>, Epist. 107, 11.</note>.</s>
					<s n="16" xml:lang="la" type="manual">Sat designavimus scelerum, satis dei longanimitatem contempsimus, patientiam calcavimus<note xml:id="fnc" type="footnote" n="c"><hi>vor</hi> calcavimus <hi>verschmiertes</hi> pa.</note><note xml:id="fn6" type="footnote" n="6">Vgl. Röm 2,4.</note>.</s>
					<s n="17" xml:lang="la" type="manual">Aderit propediem deus ultor<note xml:id="fn7" type="footnote" n="7">Vgl. Dtn 18, 19; 32, 35. Jer 51, 56.</note>.</s>
					<s n="18" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Tu orabis dominum, ut nostri misereatur, idque propter nominis sui gloriam<note xml:id="fn8" type="footnote" n="8">Vgl. Bullingers ähnliche, ausführlichere Äußerungen über diese Probleme im gleichentags verfaßten Brief an <persName ref="person154">Myconius</persName>, unten <ref target="file10880">Nr. 841</ref>, 2-49. Zu Bullingers Mißbilligung der <placeName ref="place121">Berner</placeName> Frankreichpolitik vgl. oben <ref target="file10870">Nr. 831</ref>. <persName ref="person898">Jakob Frömbd</persName> (vgl. oben <ref target="file10858">Nr. 819</ref>, 16-19).</note>.</s>
					<s n="19" xml:lang="la" type="manual"><persName ref="person898">Iacobus</persName> hic Peregrinus<note xml:id="fn9" type="footnote" n="9"><persName ref="person898">Jakob Frömbd</persName> (vgl. oben <ref target="file10858">Nr. 819</ref>, 16-19).</note> tuo nomine et quod vir bonus est, erit nobis commendatissimus.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="20" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Valebis una cum tuis omnibus.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="21" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Tiguri, 9. iunii 1536.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="22" xml:lang="la" type="auto">H. Bullingerus.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<note type="address">[Adresse auf der Rückseite:]</note>
					<s n="23" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Clarissimo viro d. Thomae <persName ref="person20">Blaurero</persName>, senatori Constantiensi prudentissimo, suo in domino fratri charissimo<note xml:id="fnd" type="footnote" n="d"><hi>Darunter von der Hand <persName ref="person20">Thomas Blarers</persName>:</hi> 14. iunii 1536; <hi>das</hi> iunii <hi>korrigiert aus</hi> iulii. <hi>Am Rand des Adreßbereichs von späterer Hand in Majuskeln.</hi> Heinricus Bullinger.</note>.</s>
				</p>
			</div>
